title.narrative: Status of the national Child Protection referral system managed by the Ministry of Social Protection (MOSP) in partnership with the Ministry of Interior (MOI), MOH and MOES

baseline.value: Child Protection referral system at national and local level does not exist

target.value: 2017:Regulations and instructions on referral pathway exist in MOSP, MOI, MOH and MOES

actual.value: 2016:The regulation is in place since December 2015. However its universal application remains challenging.

title.narrative: (NOT VALID after Dec 31 2017) Data on some forms of violence, exploitation and abuse of children are collected through routine administrative sources

baseline.value: Data collection system does not correspond to international standards and therefore is not applied

target.value: 2017:MoLSP and Juvenile Justice bodies generate accurate data (disaggregated by age, sex, region etc.) according to international standards used to plan and provide appropriate assistance to vulnerable children and children in conflict with law

actual.value: 2017:Data collection system in the area of justice for children is fully revised in line with UN indicators. title.narrative: Status of alignment of legal and normative framework with CRC concluding observations in regards to the responsibilities of social service providers and justice professionals to protect children in difficult life situations (including prevention and response)

baseline.value: Primary legislation is developed in line with CRC concluding observation, mechanisms for its implementation do not exist

target.value: 2017:Regulations and standards on provision of social services to children in difficult life situations in line with CRC concluding observations

actual.value: 2017:currently there are almost 30 bylaws available to regulate provision of services. UNICEF is supporting EU and the Government in analysis of the child care system which will inform further revision of the primary and secondary legislation.
